Keywords: Black Order , Cosmic , Deity , Eternal , Minions of Thanos , Ruler , Scientist
Real Name: Thanos
Special Powers
THANOS SHALL NOT RULE ALONE!: When Thanos starts the game, generate a Terraxia bystander.
TO USURP ETERNITY: Thanos starts the game with 6 Mortal tokens. // At the end of your turn, you may roll a d6, decreasing the result by -1 for each of his Mortal tokens. If you do, gain MISSION POINTS equal to the result, minimum 0.
INFINITY GEM APOTHEOSIS: Once per game per event listed below, when that event occurs remove one of Thanos's Mortal tokens.
*Thanos uses Willpower and succeeds
*Thanos hits an equipped character
*A friendly character named Terraxia is KO'd
*Thanos heals 2 or more clicks in a single turn
*Thanos uses Impervious and succeeds
*A character's finalized attack roll is a critical miss.
MY DIVINITY IS ABSOLUTE!: STOP. Impervious, Super Senses. Regeneration as FREE.

November 18, 2022
peeterparkker
[QUOTE]Thanos heard that Apocalypse got 4 STOP clicks and got jealous. Jokes aside, I like how this Thanos depicts him as playing his game within a game, like Thanos usually likes to try and portray himself. Ignoring his MISSION POINTS mechanic, he has really good stats, a good bystander, and his STOP clicks having the Regeneration being FREE means that either you push him while you can or he's gonna punish you for it. His steep cost is going to relegate him to home games for the most part, which is going to hurt his Viability score I give him for 300pt games. I also hate running MISSION POINTS in home games, instant loses in a causal game is fun once before it's just anti-climatic. // Thematic: 9.5/10, Viability: 5/10, Fun Factor: 7/10, leans towards home-fun.[/QUOTE] I will say that the mission points rolling at the end of the turn helps to not lose that climactic win, IMO. I agree that he does seem to toy with his opponent in this dial and that coupled with the mission point instant win feels right to me.
